@node aminetgoodies "Aminet Goodies - Writers top downloads from Aminet."
@toc reviews
============================================================================
@{b}- Aminet Goodies -@{ub}
============================================================================

Welcome to Aminet Goodies section, each issue one of our writes will list
their top 10 downloads from Aminet. For this issue there were no writers 
with the time to write up a list. So this time round I will list some of the 
fun utilities you can download for Workbench that have been recently 
uploaded to Aminet.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}AmiWeatherForecasts@{ub}

=> http://aminet.net/app/AmiWeatherForecasts1.3.lha

With more classic Amigas online than ever, it is nice to be able to take
have some modern features. AmiWeatherForecasts places the weather 
information in the Workbench menu bar. It shows the place, temperature
and an icon for cloudy, rainy, or sunny weather. You can set your location
by clicking on the menu bar and then using the drop down menu to access
settings.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}DarkForces Amiga Port@{ub}
 
=> http://aminet.net/game/shoot/tfe_darkforces.lha

Originally only released for the PC and Mac, we finally get a port for
our powered up Amigas. You need to buy the DOS port from gog.com or
steampower.com, the Mac version is not supported. It can be run on an
040 or 060, supports AGA and RTG. I find the best way to play the game
is in NTSC LowRes, which can be done via icon info, look for (FORCE PAL)
and change it to NTSC. I found with the Indivision AGA MK3 it provided
a full screen image. A great first person shooter that shows again that
the Amiga was more than capable if it had a more powerful CPU.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}AmiSSL 5.12@{ub} (updated 26th Nov 2023)
 
=> http://aminet.net/util/libs/AmiSSL-5.12-OS3.lha 

The latest update came out in October, updating to latest version will
make for a much more pleasant browsing experience, this includes using
the latest version of YAM. Since version 5 AmiSSL has been compatible
with OpenSSL 3.1. Essential update if you access the internet from your 
Amiga.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}MMULibs@{ub} (updated 26th Nov 2023)
 
=> http://aminet.net/util/libs/MMULib.lha 

Essential library if you are running an 040 or 060, especially if it is
an TF1260. If you already have MMULib installed then you do not need to
worry about this version as there have been no major changes.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}IconLib@{ub} (updated 26th Nov 2023)
 
=> http://aminet.net/util/libs/IconLib_46.4.lha 

The latest update fixes an error in WB3.0/3.1 that caused an "Object
Not Found" error when creating a new drawer in WB. New options have
also been added for WB3.0/3.1 - "DropNewIcons", "KeepNewIcons" and
"KeepColorIcons". A great utility that provides a welcome speed boost
to Workbench icons.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------

@{b}RNOSlides@{ub}
 
=> http://aminet.net/gfx/misc/RNOSlides_68k.lha

Another great utility from the house of RNO, this time around we are treated
to a slide utility that has the ability to save slideshows in two video
formats (MJPEG and AVI), and add text over images. It should be possible to 
view the slideshow within the program but I was unable to do that. However
it is still a very useful utility, especially that I can save out my 
graphics work as an AVI for presenting away from my Amiga.

============================================================================

A rather short list for this issue but I hope you will find some utilties
that you have never used before or feel like revisiting. See you next issue
when we should have another writer giving their suggestions.

@endnode


