@node inventscorner "Invents Corner"
@toc contents
============================================================================
@{b}December 2023 * I N V E N T S / C O R N E R =- @{ub} by @{"Kevin Saunders" link kevinsaunders}
============================================================================

@{b}News from Invent@{ub}

Amiga Art Contest 2023
By the time you read this Doug and I will be busy looking over all the 
entrants for this year's Amiga Art Contest, good luck everyone :) I 
have managed to submit two fun animations to this year's contest :)

@{b}Boss Machine@{ub}

Boss Machine will be the last @{b}Amiga Classic@{ub} game I will make, so I 
will be doing my very best effort. Dan and I plan on doing a live stream 
soon on Dan's youtube:

=> https://www.youtube.com/@BossMachineAmiga/videos

More assets have been created and my focus at this time has been the level 
selector screen, designing planets, screenshot thumbnails of the levels.  
Dan's very cool sprite editor have even more features, very organic spline 
controls for not only building big Bosses but paths for smaller enemies. 

I'm very impressed at what this engine can do.

@{b}Apollo-X@{ub}

Some time has been spent on the shoot 'em up for Vampire Amigas and before 
the end of the year will have some new screenshots on my Patreon Blog.  Our 
team is always very busy not only improving the ApolloOS but looking into 
future projects, hardware and software. At this stage Apollo-X is moving 
forward nicely, I am currently creating all the assets for the 
@{b}SKYRobots@{ub} level, a very mechanical scenario in space. The 
Foreground tileset is 1024x1024 pixels, which gives plenty of room for 
creative design.  I'm aiming at purely 2 parallax layers but in the Tiled 
Map Editor it is actually 4.  The reason for this is I can create a lot more 
complexity and variation by overlapping different tiles.  I'm really excited 
about this 2 player shoot 'em up. 

@{b}AmigaKit A600 GS - Amigakit@{ub}

Now that the A600 GS is in the open-public, recently shown at Amiwest 2023. 
I would like to mention that I am enjoying being part of this project. 
Recent work includes helping design the GUI - menu system as well as various 
branding and promotional materials. As you can imagine most info is under an 
NDA but as it becomes public, I can share more and I usually only post this 
info on my blog.  Currently working on further promotional materials and 
sincerely wish Amigakit great success for this exciting project.

@{b}Reshoot Proxima III@{ub}

You may have now noticed our 3rd and final game for the Reshoot series is 
now released. AmigaBill had a recent live stream on his Twitch Channel which 
was a lot of fun having the 3 main team members.  For me It was 4am in the 
morning so I was not on camera and in the chat only.  My office is part of 
the bedroom/study so it was difficult to be camera. We are extremely proud 
of this project and hope to enjoy it as much as we loved creating it.  For 
me, I wanted to create a more grungier style over say a cleaner/pixel 
perfect look. Richard certainly deserves a lot of credit overall.

@{b}Possible new Vampire Project - Dungeon Crawler game@{ub}

I have some posted news on my Patreon of some behind the scenes work on a 
Dungeon Crawler game for all Vampire Amigas.  The game will be a hybrid of 
3D dungeon and 2D rendered sprites. I'm fairly new to this project and 
currently testing out different software to create the characters.

@{b}Projects outside of the Amiga@{ub}

Before I mention future projects (and some are not even listed), this is 
partly why I will not be creating any new Classic Amiga games. Many years 
ago, I have always dreamed of making games for the Amiga, and now after 
being part of 5-6 games, I have ticked that box. As I get older (52), I 
think about what else I would like to do.  I believe the Vampire/Apollo 
Amiga needs more dedicated time to showcase what I believe is the best 
direction for the Amiga. So this is my new focus. 

An important other factor after many years of dedication all my spare 
time and more to the Amiga scene, and I would easily classify myself as 
the hardest/most productive Artist in the scene, my patreon barely gained 
any traction. Thankfully stable at 13 very valuable patrons.  When you 
think of family Life and other things in life to do, maybe its a time for a 
change, other projects and other hobbies.   The good news though is the 
Amiga scene is thriving, not as much as I would like to see but lots of 
great projects now and on the horizon.

So with that news, below is a list of games I am also working on, all games 
are for PC below. My Brother Ian and I are very close to having our 
Boulderdash/Emerald Mine clone @{b}FruityCaves@{ub} nearly complete. NOVA 
and Thrusterz 2 that i'm working with James is getting ever closer.

@{b}Ian Saunders@{ub} - Fruity Caves, Dragons Gold, Adrenaline Racer, RPG 
Shooter, Fatal Danger, Under Threat, Deep-Blue, Tank-Pong

@{b}James Roberts@{ub} - Thrusters 2, Iridium 2, Ultra Galaga, NOVA

After all of these projects, I think I need a good rest.  :)

Till next time,
Kev | Invent

www.patreon.com/KevinSaunders
@endnode

